I grew up believing that following the news makes you a better citizen. Eight years after having quit, that idea now seems ridiculous&mdash;that consuming a particularly unimaginative information product on a daily basis somehow makes you thoughtful and informed in a way that benefits society.
But I still encounter people who balk at the possibility of a smart, engaged adult quitting the daily news.
